text: The 1985 Davies and Tate British Open Championships was held at the Dunnings Mills Squash Club, East Grinstead, with the later stages being held at the Wembley Conference Centre from 15–23 April 1985. Jahangir Khan won his fourth consecutive title defeating Chris Dittmar in the final. ==Seeds== ==Draw and results== ===Final=== Jahangir Khan beat Chris Dittmar 9-3 9-2 9-5 ===Section 1=== ===Section 2=== Greg Pollard (Aus) seeded fifth withdrew before the tournament started. ==References== Category:Men's British Open Squash Championships Men's British Open Championship Men's British Open Squash Championship Men's British Open Squash Men's British Open Squash Championship Category:Squash competitions in London
title: 1985 Men's British Open Squash Championship
